message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL. The paper evaluates the performance of Open Information Extraction (OIE) on scientific texts from various disciplines, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and information retrieval. The paper also involves evaluation and analysis of the performance of OIE systems, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of state-of-the-art OIE systems, which may involve deep learning techniques, making cs.DL (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category.
